s `ListRuns(ProjectDir: x)` → server doesn't set Since → returns all runs for project\n- Global mode: calls `ListRuns(All: true)` → server doesn't set Since (because All=true) → returns all runs, client filters\n\nThe fix:\n- Server: set `Since` whenever `!req.All` (i.e., also when ProjectDir is set)\n- SQL: change `started_at >= ?` to `(completed_at >= ? OR state IN ('running', 'pending'))`\n- Global mode: now we can change it to pass `All: false` instead\n\nActually, I need to reconsider what the `All` flag really means. It looks like it's meant to indicate \"fetch all runs across all projects\", so the server skips the time filter when it's set. For global mode, I want all runs from the past hour across projects, which means I should simplify the server logic to apply the time filter whenever `All` is false, then update the SQL to check completion time and include active runs, and finally remove the client-side filtering since the server will handle it. I need to adjust the server condition to just check `!req.All` instead of the combined check, update the SQL query to include both completed runs from the past hour and any currently active runs, and then modify the global mode call to use this new behavior.\n\nNow I'm checking what tests already exist to make sure my changes won't break anything.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1363,"cache_read_input_tokens":21055,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1363},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65bc676b-72d7-4782-b6ab-9d19356a227f","uuid":"f0518ce1-60be-4e41-8cd4-71eb886de2f7"}
